he initial stage), we provide predictions for the\ntriangular flow $v_3(p_T)$ of direct photons. Additionally, we illustrate the\nmagnitude of the photon production in the partonic and hadronic phases as\nfunctions of time and local energy density. Finally, the 'cocktail' method for\nan estimation of the background photon elliptic flow, which is widely used in\nthe experimental works, is supported by the calculations within the PHSD\ntransport approach.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Apr 2015 09:04:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 1 Oct 2015 13:28:48 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 27 Oct 2015 21:20:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-02"}
